{{Culture of Botswana}}
The population of [[Botswana]] is divided into the main ethnic groups of [[Tswana people]] (79%), [[Kalanga people]] (11%), and Basarwa (or [[Bushmen]]) (3%).<ref name=nec>{{cite web |url= http://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/Africa/Botswana-ETHNIC-GROUPS.html |title=Ethnic groups - Botswana  |work=nationsencyclopedia.com |year=2012 |accessdate=15 June 2012}}</ref> The remaining 7% consist of other peoples,<ref>{{cite web |url= https://www.cia.gov/library/publications/the-world-factbook/geos/bc.html#People |title=CIA - The World Factbook  |work=cia.gov |year=2012 |accessdate=16 June 2012}}</ref> including some speaking the [[Kgalagadi language]], and 1% of non-African people.<ref name=nec/>

About 79% of the total population speak [[Setswana]] as second and first language. The ethnic Tswana is split up among eight tribes: [[Bamangwato]], [[Bakwena]], [[Bangwaketse]], [[Bakgatla]], [[Barolong]], [[Bamalete]], and [[Batlokwa]].

