There were estimated to be 60,000 '''Peruvians in Japan''' {{asof|2016|lc=on}}. The majority of them are [[Japanese Peruvians|descendants of earlier Japanese immigrants to Peru]] who have repatriated to Japan.<ref name="Takenaka">{{harvnb|Takenaka|2003|p=223}}</ref>

==Migration history==
In 1990, Japan introduced a new ethnicity-based immigration policy which aimed to encourage Japanese descendants overseas to come to Japan and fill the country's need for foreign workers.<ref name="Takenaka" /> From 1992 to 1997, data from Peru's [[Ministry of the Interior (Peru)|Ministry of the Interior]] showed Japan as the fourteenth-most popular destination for Peruvian emigrants, behind the [[Netherlands]] and ahead of [[Costa Rica]].<ref>{{harvnb|Aquino Rodríguez|1999|p=3}}</ref>

